description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Early Intervention in Psychosis Service, Horsham. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nurse Lead Practitioner (Band 6 Nurse, Part Time, Fixed Term or Secondment opportunity)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to work in a positive, enthusiastic and forward thinking team supporting people experiencing a First Episode Psychosis (FEP) and people assessed as having an At Risk Mental State (ARMS). &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be responsible for all aspects of care co-ordination, providing a range of specialist assessments and psychosocial interventions in a variety of settings. You will have previous health and social care experience of working with clients with psychosis and complex mental health and social care problems. You need to have a real commitment to and understanding of the principles of early intervention and this client group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by the team leader, existing Band 6 nursing staff and a wider MDT. You will receive support from clinical and managerial supervision, daily zoning meetings, reflective practice discussions and case formulation meetings. We offer a real commitment to support your continuing professional development through a variety of training opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Lee Raynor-Bright&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address lee.raynor-bright@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07392195392&lt;/p&gt;
